Couple random comments:<br>
<br>
CoH pulling is very useful, even for non-Fd'able pullers. That's what premptive casting or run 3 is for. When doing an ordinary exp group in a CoH-disabled zone I personally feel like I've lost an arm.<br>
<br>
West camp in PoH has horrible pathing, and is the break in spot I grew up with.<br>
<br>
Chardok pathing still suxxors. Of course, I have ally faction in chardok now, so my role there is no longer damage doing, but something much much MUCH more critical to the raid. And if I did need to use a pet stray aggro wouldn't be a problem :)<br>
<br>
I think calling magicians an effective solo class at level 60 is a joke (after watching well equipped meele's humiliate my soloing ability). Even at lower levels, considering the trickle down of gear on the servers to meele's, our strength in soloing is very much debatable. This does frighten me a little about how out of touch VI might be on magicians, but such is life.<br>
